<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Trees do not sprout, and surface or high-intensity crown fires generally kill junipers. Fires are usually moderate in intensity, burning duff and understory plants. Older trees usually survive these fires (van Wagtendonk and Fites-Kaufman 2006).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
